GIS`GeoLocationQ:
ObjectType: Symbol
Usage: GIS`GeoLocationQ[pos] returns True if pos is a valid numeric position object (either a single position or an array of position of homogeneous depths), with any of the four geo position heads: GeoPosition, GeoPositionXYZ, GeoPositionENU and GeoGridPosition. GIS`GeoLocationQ[pos, head] checks that pos has the given head. GIS`GeoLocationQ[pos, head, depth] checks that all coordinate lists have the given depth in the array. GIS`GeoLocationQ[pos, head, {mindepth, maxdepth}] checks that the homogeneous depth is between the given limits. Depths can be given as integers 0, 1, 2, ..., Infinity. GIS`GeoLocationQ[pos, head, depths, missQ] for Boolean missQ specifies whether Missing[...] objects are admitted inside the pos object. By default missQ is False.
